item.title: 'Poor choice of approaches ... ': Arnold Palmer's daughter reacts to Trump's unexpected tribute to golf legend
item.description: Arnold Palmer's daughter found Donald Trump's tribute to her father inappropriate but wasn't upset. She mentioned her father's affinity for golf and belief in the Republican Party. Trump's tribute at a Latrobe rally included a controversial anecdote. Patrick Wears will vote in the upcoming election as an unaffiliated voter.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Missing crew members found dead after fighter jet crash in Washington state
item.description: Two US Navy aviators were found dead after their EA-18G Growler jet crashed near Mount Rainier during a training flight. Search teams, including a Navy helicopter and Army Special Forces, located the wreckage in a remote, densely wooded area. The Navy has transitioned to a salvage operation and is investigating the cause of the crash.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Worked 15 minutes more than Kamala ... ' Trump visits McDonald's in Philadelphia; works the frier
item.description: Former President Donald Trump visited a McDonald's in Philadelphia, where he mocked Vice President Kamala Harris's claim of working at the chain during college. Trump aimed to connect with blue-collar voters, drawing support outside while Democrats protested across the street.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Georgia shooting: One killed, multiple injured in Albany State University
item.description: A shooting at Albany State University in Georgia during a homecoming week concert left one person dead and six injured. The incident occurred around 8:50 pm on East campus. The Georgia Bureau of Investigation is leading the probe. The identities of the victims remain undisclosed, but a 19-year-old from Atlanta has died.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Running on vibes': Pollster Nate Silver gives 24 reasons why Trump could win
item.description: Nate Silver outlines 24 reasons why Donald Trump could win the US presidential election, highlighting factors like electoral college bias, inflation, voter perceptions, and populism, along with Harris's far-left stance, media skepticism, and third-party candidates. Close poll margins emphasize the election's competitive nature.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Harris turns 60, but prefers to talk about Trump's age
item.description: Kamala Harris is celebrating her 60th birthday amid a tight election contest with Donald Trump. Both candidates, along with their high-profile surrogates, are campaigning in key battleground states like Pennsylvania. Harris takes aim at Trump's mental fitness and hosts rallies with celebrities Lizzo and Usher, while Trump campaigns vigorously despite age concerns.

item.title: 'Don't get popped': Kamala under fire over campaign ad targeting black men's love life
item.description: Kamala Harris faces criticism over a new campaign ad targeting black men's voting behavior via Instagram and Snapchat. The ad, aimed largely at women, has sparked backlash for being seen as patronizing. As the election nears, both Harris and Trump intensify their campaigns, urging early voting with celebrity endorsements.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Israeli strikes in northern Gaza leave 87 dead or missing: Gaza health ministry
item.description: Israeli airstrikes in northern Gaza resulted in at least 87 casualties, with additional injuries in Beit Lahiya. Israel's military continues operations targeting Hamas militants. The conflict has severely impacted Gaza's northern region, displacing many residents. Concurrently, the US is probing leaked documents on Israel's potential response plans to Iran's missile attack.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Yahya Sinwar's wife seen carrying $32,000 handbag in tunnel escape footage: IDF
item.description: IDF claims that former Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar's wife, Samar Muhammad Abu Zamar, was seen with a $32,000 HermÃ¨s Birkin handbag as they fled into a tunnel before the October 7 attack on Israel. Lieutenant Colonel Avichay Adraee highlighted the wealth disparity between Sinwar's family and ordinary Gazan citizens. Sinwar was killed by Israeli forces in Gaza on Wednesday.

item.title: Israel escalates Beirut bombing, kill 73 in Gaza strike, 70 projectiles cross from Lebanon within minutes: Top developments
item.description: Israeli military strikes targeted Hezbollah centers in Beirut amid escalating tensions. The attack hit intelligence headquarters and weapons facilities, with additional clashes reported in southern Lebanon. Simultaneously, the Gaza offensive resulted in significant casualties. Prime Minister Netanyahu accused Hezbollah of an assassination attempt, intensifying the conflict. Classified US documents revealing Israelâ€™s military strategies were also leaked.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Chinese food delivery industry faces downturn, workers' earnings drop by 1,000 yuan
item.description: China's USD 200 billion food delivery industry, which thrived during the pandemic, faces a downturn due to economic challenges. Delivery workers are seeing reduced incomes and job stability as consumer spending weakens. Workers now earn less despite longer hours and face increased risks from tight delivery deadlines, making it difficult to sustain livelihoods.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Russia destroys 110 Ukraine drones, four fighters injured in Dzerzhinsk
item.description: Four firefighters sustained minor shrapnel injuries after a Ukrainian drone attacked an industrial area in Dzerzhinsk, Russia. The incident was part of a broader assault where Russian air defense intercepted 110 drones, including in Moscow and other western regions, causing temporary fires and disruptions. Kyiv has previously said that its air attacks focus on infrastructure vital to Russia's war efforts in response to ongoing airstrikes on Ukraine.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Do you think Trump ever changed a tire?': Obama mocks Trump at Nevada rally
item.description: Barack Obama endorsed Kamala Harris and Minnesota Governor Tim Walz in Las Vegas, highlighting their leadership and partnership potential. Praising Walz's background and bipartisan efforts, Obama compared his abilities with Trump in a humorous light, emphasizing Harris and Walz's focus on addressing real issues and improving citizens' lives over personal concerns.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.description: The US government is investigating the leak of classified documents detailing Israelâ€™s military actions against Iran. item.title: Prabowo Subianto takes oath as eighth president of Indonesia
item.description: Prabowo Subianto, sworn in as Indonesia's eighth president on Sunday, took his oath on the Quran in Jakarta. The ceremony saw attendance from global leaders and supporters. Subianto, a former defense minister and rival to ex-President Widodo, promises continuity of existing policies. He has previously faced allegations of human rights abuses during Indonesiaâ€™s military dictatorship.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: New literary treasure: Lost ghost story by 'Dracula' author Bram Stoker discovered in Dublin
item.description: A forgotten story by Dracula author Bram Stoker, titled 'Gibbet Hill', has been unearthed in Dublin by historian Brian Cleary. Hidden for over 130 years, the story is now being publicly displayed, enriching Stoker's literary legacy and offering insight into his early works.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: In Israeli footage of the last minutes of Hamas leader's life, some see a symbol of defiance
item.description: The final moments of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar, captured in drone footage, show divergent reactions. In Gaza, some mourned or hoped for war's end, while across the Arab and Muslim world, he was seen as a heroic martyr. Israelis celebrated his demise, but critics argue that his death ignites further defiance among Palestinians.

item.title: 'We have power to change this moment': Usher endorses Harris; MAGA calls out singer's links to Diddy
item.description: Usher endorsed Kamala Harris for U.S. President at a rally in Atlanta. He highlighted her commitment to inclusivity and urged voter turnout in Georgia. Usher followed singer Lizzo, who had previously joined Harris' campaign. Some people criticized Usher for his alleged ties to controversial events, but his endorsement generated significant enthusiasm among Harris' supporters.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: G7 defence ministers concerned by attacks on peacekeepers, vow Kyiv support
item.description: G7 defence ministers met in Naples amid multiple conflicts, expressing concern over Lebanon's situation and pledging unwavering support for Ukraine. The ministers emphasised continued military assistance to Ukraine and called for Iran to stop supporting Hamas and Hezbollah. There were also discussions on strengthening the UN peacekeeping mission in Lebanon and the impact of global instability.
